## Shortcuts
- CURSOR:PAIR — act as pair programmer, suggest alternatives, weigh best course of action.
- RFC — refactor code per instructions.

## Naming Conventions
- Classes: PascalCase
- Variables, functions, methods: camelCase
- Files, directories: kebab-case
- Constants: UPPERCASE

## Git Commits
- Brief title, details in body
- Always follow conventional commit format (feat:, fix:, chore: etc.)
- Two newlines after title

## Code Quality
- Avoid `any`
- Proper error handling everywhere
- No code duplication